When we presented on our paper, I talked about how this feels like a little bit of history repeating:

Where modality of instruction appeared to matter was as a second order variable: online learning that did not facilitate interactions and was employed specifically during time periods of quarantines and social distancing can exacerbate feelings of loneliness or isolation, BUT

In our review, a few quality studies looked at the root causes to mental health declines during the pandemic. This visual summarizes a host of moderating variables we identified in studies on mental health and pandemic (those that mentioned or examined online learning directly).
